# Plesk License Management

The plesk license can be issued from the Odin management panel.

Plesk has different type license and they are charging different amount for license from each customer. The charges are based on the account level.

> Our account level is SILVER

## Activate Plesk License

- Login to the Odin Management Panel. Then click on Buy New License. It has a total of 6 steps

```diagram

```

- 1st step is Choose Key Group. You can choose Plesk 12 Lease Keys and click on the Cart icon.

```diagram

```

- 2nd step is Choose the Key. Select the License type from the list and click on the Cart icon

```diagram

```

- 3rd Step is Add Features to the selected license key. Do not add any features if customer not requested. Just scroll down the page the click on the Next button
- 4th Step is Order Confirmation. Review the order and select the parallel license agreement then click on Confirm. If you want edit the order again then click on Edit Order.

```diagram

```


- 5th Step: Add notes on the key. It is not mandatory.
- 6th Step is the Key Delivery. Select the address you want to deliver the key. Use the default settings.

## Terminate the Plesk License

- Get the license number from https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1__pqSmZy6qLQ_pacJpkU3SgnKGdmgBxbKwWxGMrVaSU/edit#gid=0
There are 3 pages. 3rd one is the terminated license numbers
1. Dedicated - The License numbers of Dedicated Customers
2. VPS - The License numbers of colossuscloud Customers

- Login to the Odin panel and click on Manage License.
- Put the Key Number in the Search box and search for it. 

```diagram

```

- Click on the License Number >> Click on More option and Select the Terminate

```diagram

```


## How to get the Plesk Activation Code from a license

- Get the license number
- Go to the Odin panel and search with the license number to get the license details. 
- Now go to Retrieve License >> Show Activation code. The you will get the activation code linked to that license number.
